\paperw12240\paperh15840\margl1800\margr1800\margt1440\margb1440\f0\fs24\cf0
\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Maybe have it so that this is the final battle to end all battles. This one was final. She had made a deal.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The northern army, sweeping away to her right, belonged to her. She had worked these last few hundred years pulling the good peoples of the world up from despair to fight for her god\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s purpose. Her god had helped, but she had done the legwork.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Their enemy was innumerable, but more disorganized, drawn as they were from the filth of men, women, and demons. These miscreants poured forth from frothing holes near the southern seas. They sustained their long march to reach this chosen site by consuming each other. They chewed as they walked, with bits and pieces falling from their mouths. Their long battle line left a trail of picked clean bones behind them. Those who had eaten much had grown near to the size of god-eaters. Tall as small mountains, these immobile mounds of flesh had to be rope-hauled along rolling logs, brought here that they might birth more demons to swell their ranks.}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 yet the neglected state roads and concrete pastures that trimmed every dried river bend reminded her home. There were sections of the Red River where cypress knees still cordoned off \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91wild parts\u8217\'92, but every two-hundred yards or so her raft would float past a massive stone cairn. At eye-level these grim monuments blended in to the sense of place, but she knew how they pocked the landscape, how their broad  bases flared up like pimples amongst the greenlands all way into fertile portion. It was depressing. The whole surface of the world was crusted over with history. It made her envious of the past, being able to walk or ride for days or weeks without sight or sound of another human being.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 There would be significantly living creatures after today.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The world had been through too many ages. There wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t enough to go around.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 For the next three hours, system statuses and observations were read out, a final redundancy meant to focus the crew. Moto knew it was an unnecessary procedure because he knew that he, Oya, and Alberto had each dreamed of this moment a thousand times over, and they had each run through the simulations a thousand times more. Still, he kept a little motivating fear around in  his thoughts to keep him sharp, because while the mission of The Experiment was worth dying for, absent-minded mistakes were not. Even after this final systems check wrapped up, and the three settled into The Experiment\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s central command module, Moto kept on considering the many manners in which he might die during the next half-hour. Oya was the last to float in.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 At the moment the planet was shifting just out of frame, but she could still make out the Atlantic Ocean with its magnificent phytoplankton blooms, thousands of miles long, glowing prussian-blue in whirling ocean gyres. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The mountains there run like blisters, compliments of the tectonic crossroads upon which they sit, and the rivers resemble old, dry wounds scabbed over with salt. There is a very real sense of the mantle\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s boiling written into the crust. From here, it looks like life in the region evaporated centuries ago. Most of the colors dip into grey. Not enough green. It must be terrible down there.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen saw all this, and decided it was time. He blinked out of existence, then reappeared in front othe}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 His bright being stunned all eyes into submission. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Celebrants of war .}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Though they did not worship him, they bowed. Though the hated him, they would not strike out, not here, for even they would abide by the oldest rule: neither of the god of gods could be killed in an act of treat.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A meeting of the Envoys\u8221\'94, Solraheen said. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Whale demon with a human brain. The demon writhed. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where\u8221\'94 it rasped.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Solraheen pointed to the mountain top from which he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d come.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 During the dances several \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91masters of ceremonies,\u8217\'92 bearing bunches of palm-leaves, went up and down, keeping a clear space\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 driving back the circle of\~spectators by striking these on legs and feet. Suddenly the performers scattered, leaving two of their number alone in the centre. These bent and touched the ground with their fingers, then almost immediately gripped and after a struggle, which caused the wildest excitement among the spectators, the taller and slighter of the two flung the other to earth and seated himself firmly astride the prostrate form\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to be lifted upon the shoulders of a friend and thus borne round amid the plaudits of the multitude.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So it will be,\u8221\'94 the demon king said.}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0}